# Job Digest — 2026-03-23

Track: core_crypto
Run timestamp: 2026-03-23 08:00:00 CET
Sources checked: 10
New roles found: 1
High-signal matches: 1

## Executive summary

Found 1 new role worth attention. Monash has a technically strong lattice/PET postdoc that aligns well with Jonas's background, but it is an older Australia-based academic posting and should be status-checked before acting. No new industry role cleared the bar today.

## Recommended actions

- Check whether the Monash `Post-Doc in Lattice-Based Cryptography and/or Privacy-Enhancing Technologies` role is still active; it is still listed on IACR, but the posting dates back to September 11, 2025 and says it will be filled as soon as a suitable candidate is found.
- Skip PQShield's `Software Prototype Intern – Post-Quantum Cryptography` unless Jonas explicitly wants internship-level or temporary product prototyping work.
- Skip the newly surfaced Web3-heavy smart-contract and blockchain-infrastructure roles unless Jonas wants to pivot away from core cryptography / PETs into that ecosystem.

## Strong matches

### 1. Post-Doc in Lattice-Based Cryptography and/or Privacy-Enhancing Technologies — Monash University
Link: https://www.iacr.org/jobs/item/4036
Location: Melbourne, Australia
Remote: unknown
Team / domain: lattice-based cryptography / privacy-enhancing technologies / zero-knowledge proofs
Posted: 2025-09-11
Source: IACR Jobs

Why it matches:
- The posting is explicitly centered on lattice-based cryptography and privacy-enhancing technologies, including advanced cryptographic tools and zero-knowledge proofs.
- It requires significant prior research experience in those areas plus a completed or near-complete PhD, which lines up closely with Jonas's documented applied-cryptography profile.
- The role sits squarely in cryptography research rather than generic software, product security, or blockchain application work.

Possible concerns:
- Melbourne relocation and the academic postdoc structure make this a materially bigger practical commitment than a Europe-based industry role.
- The listing is relatively old as of March 23, 2026 and says it will be filled when a suitable candidate is found, so the live status should be confirmed quickly.

Fit score: 8/10
Recommendation: watch

## Borderline / maybe

No borderline new roles were strong enough to keep in today's digest.

## Roles filtered out

- University College Cork — `PostDoc (or Research Assistant) in Privacy-enhancing Technologies` — explicit deadline was December 19, 2025, which is already past as of March 23, 2026.
- PQShield — `Software Prototype Intern – Post-Quantum Cryptography` — internship scope and 6-month duration are too junior / temporary for Jonas's profile.
- Least Authority — `Smart Contracts Security Researcher & Engineer` — workable location setup, but the visible posting is dated January 25, 2024 and is too centered on smart-contract auditing for Jonas's clearest strengths.
- Ethereum Foundation — `Stateless Consensus Intern` — explicit student / internship framing and distributed-systems emphasis make it a weak fit for this track.
- QEDIT — `Cryptography Engineer` — already present in `shared/seen_jobs.md`.
- Zama — `Rust Engineer, Coprocessor`, `Rust Engineer, Relayer`, `Developer Experience Engineer`, and QA-oriented roles — none were clean enough fits after location constraints and blockchain-platform specialization.

## Source notes

- IACR Jobs — one reportable Monash postdoc; one UCC PET role was filtered out for a past deadline; additional listings were weaker fits.
- PQShield — one new PQC internship was found and filtered; the hardware verification role remains a duplicate.
- Zama — active roles appear concentrated in blockchain platform, developer-experience, and QA work; none were clear reportable fits.
- Roseman Labs — only Dutch-speaking solution/customer roles were visible.
- Duality Technologies — no reportable cryptography/PET opening surfaced from the careers page on this pass.
- QEDIT — the existing cryptography engineer role is still visible but already seen.
- Least Authority — the visible smart-contract security role was filtered for age and specialization.
- Trail of Bits — the careers page loaded, but direct openings did not render beyond a talent-pipeline link on this pass.
- Partisia Blockchain — no concrete openings were listed beyond a general CV submission form.
